</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>If you offer multiple services, choose the category that represents your highest-revenue service as your primary.</p>
<h3>Complete Every Field</h3>
<p>Incomplete profiles rank lower. Fill out everything Google offers.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Business name:</strong> Exact legal name. Do not stuff keywords like "Best Pool Service Dallas."</li>
<li><strong>Description:</strong> 750 characters. Cover services, service area, years in business, and what sets you apart.</li>
<li><strong>Services:</strong> List every service with a description. Pool cleaning, chemical balancing, equipment repair, pump replacement, leak detection, pool opening, pool closing.</li>
<li><strong>Appointment URL:</strong> Link to your scheduling page or contact form.</li>
<li><strong>Hours:</strong> Accurate hours. Update for seasonal changes.</li>
<li><strong>Photos:</strong> Pools you have serviced, before-and-after shots, team photos, branded trucks. Upload 5 to 10 new photos per month.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Post Weekly</h3>
<p>GBP posts signal an active business. Post at least once per week.</p>
<p><strong>Post ideas for pool companies:</strong>
- Seasonal tips (pool opening checklist, winterization reminders)
- Before-and-after photos of cleanings or repairs
- Special offers (first cleaning discount, seasonal packages)
- Educational content (water chemistry basics, filter maintenance)
- Weather-related alerts (freeze warnings, algae season prep)</p>
<p>Each post should include a call to action: "Book Now," "Get a Free Quote," or "Call Today."</p>
